definition: problem or question solved for illustrative purposes in the classroom/practice question (used in preparation for an exam)/sample question
topic/problem for discussion/exam question/subject/to inscribe/to mention/CL:個|个[ge4],道[dao4]

sentences.english: Let's do an example just to see how it goes.
sentences.chinese: 我们做个例题，来看看它是怎么回事。

sentences.english: At la- st, the algorithm works, we used several standard examples to test the numerical results.
sentences.chinese: 最后，我们用几种典型例题检验了该算法的实际效果。

sentences.english: Illustrate the computation procedure of the suggested method by examples.
sentences.chinese: 用例题展示了所建议方法的计算过程。

sentences.english: Numerical examples exhibit the multi-physical coupling phenomena of biomaterials.
sentences.chinese: 数值例题展示了生物材料中的多物理耦合现象。

sentences.english: This paper shows the important roles of variable upper limit definite integral derivative through several examples.
sentences.chinese: 通过例题给出变上限定积分求导的几个应用。

sentences.english: There are also three problems follow each example.
sentences.chinese: 每道例题后面又跟着三个练习题。

sentences.english: Before I do the example, let me just say in a different language.
sentences.chinese: 做例题之前，我先用另一种方式表达一下。

sentences.english: Microsoft examinations detailed explanation of the calendar year analytic questions, as examples.
sentences.chinese: 微软考试详尽的解释，历年试题解析，例题等。

sentences.english: Let us work out a very simple example.
sentences.chinese: 接下来我讲一个简单的例题。

sentences.english: Let's do a second example with the same sphere.
sentences.chinese: 还是这个球面，我们来做第二个例题。

sentences.english: We will do more examples in a bit.
It proved that the 4th-order BDF discrete circuit model has considerably high simulating precision.
sentences.chinese: 例题计算结果表明，该模型具有较高的仿真精度。
